{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Shared","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/AppStorageKey","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/FileStorageKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"]}],"metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.10","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Sharing state","anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Shared","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will require that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SignUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, if you want any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistenceReaderKey\/fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"text":" in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistenceReaderKey\/appStorage(_:)-4l5b"},{"type":"text","text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"key:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistenceReaderKey\/fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"reference"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of "},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" article","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "